1
00:02:20,308 --> 00:02:22,298
THE CRIMSON RIVERS

2
00:05:15,391 --> 00:05:17,014
We will touch base in two hours.

3
00:05:18,391 --> 00:05:19,847
- Which way do we go?
- There.

4
00:05:19,848 --> 00:05:22,339
Okay? See you later, guys.

5
00:05:30,683 --> 00:05:32,223
Can I help you?

6
00:05:32,724 --> 00:05:33,802
Got a light?

7
00:05:33,803 --> 00:05:35,515
Who let you through?

8
00:05:35,891 --> 00:05:38,675
Your men. Commissioner Pierre Niemans.

9
00:05:40,891 --> 00:05:43,592
Just you?
Paris said they'd send a unit.

10
00:05:43,593 --> 00:05:45,342
What the hell?

11
00:05:45,724 --> 00:05:46,755
I am the unit.

12
00:05:51,766 --> 00:05:52,430
Captain...

13
00:05:53,974 --> 00:05:57,387
I didn't drive all night
to wage war with cops.

14
00:05:59,516 --> 00:06:00,713
What's the lowdown?

15
00:06:02,349 --> 00:06:03,723
Follow me.

16
00:06:06,183 --> 00:06:09,880
Two days ago, the college dean
reported Remy Callois missing.

17
00:06:10,308 --> 00:06:12,048
Thirty-two years old, single.

18
00:06:12,049 --> 00:06:15,804
Remy lectured at the college.
He was also the librarian.

19
00:06:16,016 --> 00:06:17,841
An upper echelon job there.

20
00:06:18,349 --> 00:06:22,259
According to the Dean,
Remy was punctual and hardworking.

21
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:24,388
He never showed up late.

22
00:06:24,974 --> 00:06:28,676
Yesterday afternoon a young
mountain climber found his body.

23
00:06:29,891 --> 00:06:31,514
Why call in the homicide squad?

24
00:06:34,641 --> 00:06:37,129
We're not used to this kind of stuff.

25
00:06:37,130 --> 00:06:38,505
Why?

26
00:06:39,016 --> 00:06:43,223
His body was strung up there.
At 50 meters.

27
00:06:54,683 --> 00:06:59,008
GUERNON University, 500 meters

28
00:07:04,183 --> 00:07:07,762
You're from the homicide unit,
but not really, is that it?

29
00:07:07,974 --> 00:07:09,005
That's it.

30
00:07:11,724 --> 00:07:13,680
We never dealt with you before.

31
00:07:15,724 --> 00:07:16,968
You're lucky.

32
00:07:23,891 --> 00:07:27,304
"Happy is he who penetrates
the hidden cause of things."

33
00:07:44,558 --> 00:07:47,046
What's this college doing here?

34
00:07:47,516 --> 00:07:48,760
It's no ordinary college.

35
00:07:49,849 --> 00:07:52,633
It provides its own electricity,
its own water.

36
00:07:52,634 --> 00:07:54,424
It even has a hospital.

37
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:58,672
1,200 students.
100 professors and researchers.

38
00:07:58,673 --> 00:08:00,882
One of Europe's oldest universities.

39
00:08:04,266 --> 00:08:07,548
In case of a snowstorm,
it can survive for a month.

40
00:08:08,808 --> 00:08:11,639
The Dean is
like the mayor of the valley.

41
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:13,757
He runs most of the region.

42
00:08:14,558 --> 00:08:17,472
Here's where they
form future Bill Gates.

43
00:08:19,808 --> 00:08:20,969
Future what?

44
00:08:22,724 --> 00:08:25,592
Future Bill Gates.

45
00:09:19,724 --> 00:09:22,011
The hospital's attached to the college?

46
00:09:22,266 --> 00:09:24,754
It's open to everyone in the region.

47
00:09:24,755 --> 00:09:26,556
We all get free health care.

48
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,722
We work a lot with them.

49
00:09:31,016 --> 00:09:32,923
There's even a maternity wing.

50
00:09:46,891 --> 00:09:50,718
This is Commissioner Niemans.
He will be helping out on this case.

51
00:09:50,719 --> 00:09:53,592
I was in your Criminology class in 1987.

52
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:55,003
Did you start yet?

53
00:09:55,004 --> 00:09:56,888
I haven't cut the cord.

54
00:09:56,889 --> 00:09:58,170
Can we see?

55
00:09:58,171 --> 00:10:01,963
I figured you'd want to see him intact.
It's incredible.

56
00:10:01,964 --> 00:10:03,931
The work of a real madman.

57
00:10:05,308 --> 00:10:07,263
He strove for the fetal position.

58
00:10:08,058 --> 00:10:09,088
What position?

59
00:10:09,974 --> 00:10:13,589
The fetal. Like a fetus
in its mother's belly.

60
00:10:36,641 --> 00:10:39,046
He's been dead for 48 hours.

61
00:10:40,224 --> 00:10:43,009
Examination reveals
traces of incisions...

62
00:10:43,474 --> 00:10:47,136
on the shoulders, arms,
elbows and thighs...

63
00:10:47,641 --> 00:10:50,390
made by a sharp instrument.
A carpet cutter.

64
00:10:50,641 --> 00:10:52,548
Can you cut the cord?

65
00:10:56,308 --> 00:10:58,132
Four broken ribs.

66
00:10:58,133 --> 00:11:01,673
Arms broken at the shoulders and elbows.

67
00:11:01,933 --> 00:11:07,763
Multiple fractures: tibia, hip...I will
put it all in a detailed report.

68
00:11:08,308 --> 00:11:12,514
The hands were amputated before
he died, with an axe...

69
00:11:12,515 --> 00:11:16,723
the stumps cauterized to avoid
his bleeding to death.

70
00:11:17,683 --> 00:11:21,214
The killer obviously wanted
to keep his victim alive.

71
00:11:55,474 --> 00:11:57,299
I wouldn't do that...

72
00:11:57,516 --> 00:11:59,921
He carved out the eyes like a surgeon.

73
00:12:01,641 --> 00:12:03,797
Operating on a live patient.

74
00:12:04,683 --> 00:12:06,589
What the fuck is this shit?

75
00:12:06,590 --> 00:12:10,765
The sockets were filled with rain.
It's being analyzed.

76
00:12:11,016 --> 00:12:14,962
There's a good eye doctor in Guernon.
He may shed some light on this.

77
00:12:17,599 --> 00:12:19,424
How long did it take him to die?

78
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:24,680
I'd have to cut him open,
but I'd say five hours.

79
00:12:27,641 --> 00:12:29,596
The size and precision
of the wounds...

80
00:12:30,391 --> 00:12:34,171
indicate that he wanted
his victim conscious...

81
00:12:34,474 --> 00:12:37,141
but in the greatest
possible state of pain.

82
00:12:49,516 --> 00:12:52,715
Check every prison,
every loony bin and sect.

83
00:12:52,716 --> 00:12:54,969
Every trail, refuge and ski slope.

84
00:12:54,970 --> 00:12:59,632
Run random identity checks on drivers
in a 160 kilometer radius.

85
00:12:59,633 --> 00:13:04,173
Dig up evidence of similar mutilations
in the past 20 years.

86
00:13:04,174 --> 00:13:07,430
Talk to possible witnesses
and Callois's colleagues.

87
00:13:07,431 --> 00:13:09,755
Anyone who knew his itinerary.

88
00:13:09,756 --> 00:13:12,931
Find out where it rained
in the past two days.

89
00:13:13,224 --> 00:13:17,549
Find anything: witnesses, clues...
you have two hours.

90
00:13:49,016 --> 00:13:50,639
Doctor Cherneze Ophthalmologist

91
00:14:24,183 --> 00:14:25,261
Who's there?

92
00:14:28,724 --> 00:14:30,051
Who's there?

93
00:14:32,058 --> 00:14:33,515
Who is it?

94
00:14:34,474 --> 00:14:35,588
Why won't you talk?

95
00:14:37,641 --> 00:14:38,221
Doctor.

96
00:14:39,974 --> 00:14:40,804
- Who are you?
- What's going on?

97
00:14:41,808 --> 00:14:43,384
Get the dog out of here.

98
00:14:43,849 --> 00:14:46,634
It's nothing. Go home.
Everything's alright.

99
00:14:47,349 --> 00:14:48,629
See you on Tuesday.

100
00:14:50,433 --> 00:14:51,179
Who are you?

101
00:14:51,849 --> 00:14:55,345
Commissioner Niemans. Sorry,
dogs scare me shitless.

102
00:14:56,891 --> 00:14:59,806
Dogs are not to fear.
Just their masters.

103
00:15:02,974 --> 00:15:04,633
How can I help you?

104
00:15:08,974 --> 00:15:11,344
I am investigating Remy Callois's death.

105
00:15:12,808 --> 00:15:14,300
I heard about it.

106
00:15:15,724 --> 00:15:17,004
How awful.

107
00:15:19,058 --> 00:15:20,550
Did you know him?

108
00:15:21,224 --> 00:15:23,215
I knew his father.

109
00:15:24,099 --> 00:15:26,553
We went to college together.

110
00:15:28,974 --> 00:15:30,799
Did you teach at the college?

111
00:15:32,058 --> 00:15:33,550
For 20 years.

112
00:15:34,558 --> 00:15:39,215
But I stopped teaching in 1982.

113
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:42,594
Why?

114
00:15:44,558 --> 00:15:46,050
Difference of opinion.

115
00:15:47,974 --> 00:15:48,969
With the Dean?

116
00:15:49,433 --> 00:15:54,090
I don't understand.
What's the link between me and Remy?

117
00:15:54,808 --> 00:15:58,256
I have some pictures
I'd like your opinion of.

118
00:16:03,099 --> 00:16:04,806
He was tortured?

119
00:16:05,349 --> 00:16:06,842
For several hours.

120
00:16:08,433 --> 00:16:09,925
How horrible...

121
00:16:12,933 --> 00:16:14,509
I didn't know.

122
00:16:19,183 --> 00:16:20,722
No hands?

123
00:16:20,723 --> 00:16:22,300
Nor eyes.

124
00:16:22,516 --> 00:16:26,094
That's why I am here.
To understand these mutilations.

125
00:16:26,095 --> 00:16:28,056
How would I know?

126
00:16:28,724 --> 00:16:30,431
What exactly do you treat?

127
00:16:30,849 --> 00:16:33,931
Genetic afflictions concerning the eyes.

128
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:39,509
Hereditary diseases transmitted
from one generation to the next.

129
00:16:39,974 --> 00:16:43,421
They strike isolated areas
and with the college...

130
00:16:43,422 --> 00:16:44,972
What about the college?

131
00:16:44,973 --> 00:16:48,672
Teachers have been marrying
among themselves for ages.

132
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:51,717
The bloodlines are weak, worn out.

133
00:16:52,808 --> 00:16:55,131
Genetic problems keep popping up.

134
00:16:56,724 --> 00:16:58,300
The ransom of the elite.

135
00:16:59,183 --> 00:17:02,762
I thought the professors' kids
were prodigies.

136
00:17:03,933 --> 00:17:05,176
They are.

137
00:17:05,974 --> 00:17:07,467
I don't get it.

138
00:17:10,766 --> 00:17:12,721
Over the past two generations...

139
00:17:13,183 --> 00:17:15,339
the situation has reversed.

140
00:17:16,808 --> 00:17:19,759
The native mountain children
are getting sick.

141
00:17:20,933 --> 00:17:22,970
Like the boy you just saw.

142
00:17:27,183 --> 00:17:31,887
Could there be a connection between
the mutilations and the diseases?

143
00:17:34,974 --> 00:17:39,098
Hands and eyes are the body parts
that belong to us alone.

144
00:17:40,558 --> 00:17:43,721
They're different from anyone else's,
like with DNA.

145
00:17:44,141 --> 00:17:47,554
They're our biological identity.

146
00:17:50,141 --> 00:17:53,305
Your killer is giving you hints
as to his motive.

147
00:17:57,766 --> 00:17:59,921
And he starts stabbing away.

148
00:17:59,922 --> 00:18:02,635
He stabs the dog, stabs the guy...

149
00:18:03,224 --> 00:18:06,056
grabs the bag and throws
the knife under the car.

150
00:18:06,057 --> 00:18:08,629
Seriously, Paris is full of psychos.

151
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,050
The subway. The cops.

152
00:18:10,051 --> 00:18:13,340
Robocops.
"Hand over your ticket, please."

153
00:18:13,341 --> 00:18:15,968
What the hell?
I am happy with my cows.

154
00:18:15,969 --> 00:18:20,881
I am happy here. Fresh air.
It's amazing here.

155
00:18:20,882 --> 00:18:22,847
Take a look at my cows.

156
00:18:23,308 --> 00:18:24,931
Paris sucks.

157
00:18:29,308 --> 00:18:30,765
Kids doing this shit.

158
00:18:33,224 --> 00:18:35,344
- It's the County Mounties.
- Hi, kids.

159
00:18:35,345 --> 00:18:37,387
- How's it hanging?
- What's up?

160
00:18:37,388 --> 00:18:39,679
Cool it...

161
00:18:40,391 --> 00:18:41,670
Can we go now?

162
00:18:43,683 --> 00:18:45,638
Happy squirrel hunting.

163
00:19:12,849 --> 00:19:14,390
You want the roach?

164
00:19:16,641 --> 00:19:17,755
You smoke?

165
00:19:18,766 --> 00:19:21,052
- I always have.
- You didn't before.

166
00:19:21,053 --> 00:19:22,634
Now I do.

167
00:19:23,058 --> 00:19:24,680
You're smoking on duty.

168
00:19:24,681 --> 00:19:26,258
He does.

169
00:19:26,259 --> 00:19:28,138
You're lower on the totem pole.

170
00:19:28,139 --> 00:19:29,717
Where does that put you?

171
00:19:30,224 --> 00:19:34,052
Harry and Sally.
Why did you come for me?

172
00:19:34,053 --> 00:19:36,380
The cemetery got robbed last night.

173
00:19:36,381 --> 00:19:38,298
The word is "desecrated".

174
00:19:38,299 --> 00:19:40,927
The elementary school got desecrated, too.

175
00:19:40,928 --> 00:19:43,256
The word is "robbed", dick wad.

176
00:19:43,766 --> 00:19:46,385
Two in a day.
We're back in business, guys.

177
00:19:47,016 --> 00:19:50,796
Let's start with the cemetery.
I am riding high today.

178
00:19:51,433 --> 00:19:52,890
Pass the joint.

179
00:19:54,308 --> 00:19:55,847
- What now?
- Nothing.

180
00:19:55,848 --> 00:19:58,089
- You're sulking.
- Because you're smoking.

181
00:19:58,090 --> 00:20:00,172
Do I sulk when you drink?

182
00:20:00,173 --> 00:20:02,719
Cut the crap.
You sound like two old hookers.

183
00:20:15,933 --> 00:20:19,381
You're here for the desecration.
Follow me.

184
00:20:20,058 --> 00:20:21,087
I am okay.

185
00:20:21,088 --> 00:20:23,221
It's the girl's mausoleum.

186
00:20:23,724 --> 00:20:26,213
The only mausoleum in the cemetery.

187
00:20:27,516 --> 00:20:29,139
When I got here this morning...

188
00:20:30,683 --> 00:20:33,006
this is what I found.

189
00:20:33,974 --> 00:20:38,762
It's those skinheads.
They're always hanging around here.

190
00:20:41,433 --> 00:20:44,596
- We have skinheads?
- Not skinheads. Just kids.

191
00:20:44,933 --> 00:20:47,847
- Kiddie skinheads?
- Just kid kids.

192
00:20:49,849 --> 00:20:51,389
Did this ever happen before?

193
00:20:51,390 --> 00:20:53,595
The first time.

194
00:21:07,474 --> 00:21:09,880
"1972-1982".

195
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:13,054
She didn't make it too far.

196
00:21:15,058 --> 00:21:17,889
Stop that. You have no right.

197
00:21:17,890 --> 00:21:21,055
You need her parents' say-so.
I know the law.

198
00:21:21,056 --> 00:21:23,463
Relax. No problem.

199
00:21:23,464 --> 00:21:25,512
Where can I find the parents?

200
00:21:25,513 --> 00:21:27,928
Her mother was crazy.

201
00:21:28,224 --> 00:21:30,381
She said the devil killed her kid.

202
00:21:31,558 --> 00:21:32,387
The devil?

203
00:21:32,388 --> 00:21:33,801
You heard me.

204
00:21:38,641 --> 00:21:41,390
Judith Herault
14 April 1972 - 23 September 1982

205
00:21:44,641 --> 00:21:46,346
Where are your skinheads?

206
00:21:46,347 --> 00:21:48,258
A warehouse in town.

207
00:21:48,641 --> 00:21:50,547
Let's pay them a little visit.

208
00:21:50,548 --> 00:21:53,799
First the school.
The principal's expecting us.

209
00:21:54,391 --> 00:21:55,220
What's she missing?

210
00:21:56,308 --> 00:21:59,306
Nothing's missing.
That's what's so strange.

211
00:21:59,766 --> 00:22:02,337
I have never seen you.
Are you new here?

212
00:22:03,266 --> 00:22:04,379
Is it that obvious?

213
00:22:04,380 --> 00:22:06,796
What did you do to end up here?

214
00:22:06,797 --> 00:22:10,635
Cops are like teachers.
We can't always choose our school.

215
00:22:10,636 --> 00:22:14,504
Tell me about it. For 14 years,
I have asked to be transferred.

216
00:22:14,505 --> 00:22:16,050
Now it's too late.

217
00:22:22,766 --> 00:22:26,214
They broke in here,
where we keep school records.

218
00:22:26,724 --> 00:22:29,426
They went about it extremely carefully.

219
00:22:40,058 --> 00:22:42,380
Are you sure nothing's missing?

220
00:22:42,381 --> 00:22:45,969
Nothing at all. I checked this morning.
It's so weird.

221
00:22:45,970 --> 00:22:47,515
I don't understand.

222
00:22:48,308 --> 00:22:49,469
Okay.

223
00:22:51,808 --> 00:22:54,759
File a complaint at the station
this afternoon.

224
00:22:55,099 --> 00:22:56,721
So the investigation's over?

225
00:22:56,722 --> 00:22:59,759
What can I say?
No theft, no investigation.

226
00:23:00,349 --> 00:23:02,470
Have a nice day. Goodbye.

227
00:23:03,599 --> 00:23:05,008
Goodbye, Detective.

228
00:23:05,009 --> 00:23:07,885
"Detective" is passé. It's
"Lieutenant" now.

229
00:23:21,891 --> 00:23:24,758
Just a second.
How long have you been here?

230
00:23:24,759 --> 00:23:26,590
Not as long as you seem to think.

231
00:23:26,591 --> 00:23:29,472
If I say a name,
could it ring a bell?

232
00:23:29,473 --> 00:23:30,718
Try me.

233
00:23:30,719 --> 00:23:32,549
Judith Herault.

234
00:23:33,349 --> 00:23:35,256
Was she one of my students?

235
00:23:35,257 --> 00:23:36,924
She died in 1982.

236
00:23:36,925 --> 00:23:39,588
- Should I check?
- I'd appreciate it.

237
00:23:40,474 --> 00:23:42,346
You think there's a connection?

238
00:23:42,933 --> 00:23:44,758
You tell me.

239
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:51,129
I wonder if she's the
one who got run over.

240
00:23:51,130 --> 00:23:52,171
Run over?

241
00:23:52,172 --> 00:23:55,880
Killed in a highway accident.
It was terrible.

242
00:23:55,881 --> 00:23:57,005
What else?

243
00:23:57,006 --> 00:24:00,879
It was a truck. The mother was there.
She became insane.

244
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:03,094
How can I find the mother?

245
00:24:03,095 --> 00:24:04,545
What's wrong?

246
00:24:05,016 --> 00:24:08,844
The pages are torn out.
The pages from '81 and '82.

247
00:24:09,516 --> 00:24:10,630
Bingo.

248
00:24:11,266 --> 00:24:14,797
Any pictures?
Class photos, stuff like that.

249
00:24:18,724 --> 00:24:20,680
The pictures are missing, too.

250
00:24:28,183 --> 00:24:29,261
I will be right back.

251
00:24:37,266 --> 00:24:38,545
What's the problem?

252
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:41,222
Any highway patrolmen here?

253
00:24:41,558 --> 00:24:43,928
Not one. They're all out to lunch.

254
00:24:45,641 --> 00:24:47,050
What for?

255
00:24:47,308 --> 00:24:49,796
I need some info. I am a cop myself.

256
00:24:51,891 --> 00:24:53,299
Information about what?

257
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:57,054
An accident that happened
around here 20 years ago.

258
00:24:58,058 --> 00:25:00,629
It's your lucky day. They
call me "gravedigger".

259
00:25:01,141 --> 00:25:04,553
Over the past 27 years, I have
seen 248, no, wait...

260
00:25:04,554 --> 00:25:07,253
249 accidents entailing deaths.

261
00:25:07,254 --> 00:25:10,465
On our part of the highway alone.
30 kilometers.

262
00:25:10,466 --> 00:25:13,638
Cops and firemen get all the attention.

263
00:25:13,639 --> 00:25:16,212
But we're the first guys on the scene.

264
00:25:16,213 --> 00:25:19,092
It's all in here.
What do you want to know?

265
00:25:19,093 --> 00:25:21,967
- You can use that?
- What do you think?

266
00:25:21,968 --> 00:25:26,763
I am looking for the parents of a girl
killed in '82. Judith Herault.

267
00:25:27,641 --> 00:25:29,431
That sounds familiar.

268
00:25:30,183 --> 00:25:32,636
- Judith Herault...
- H..E..R..A..U..L..T.

269
00:25:35,808 --> 00:25:39,256
Search by victim's name: Judith Herault

270
00:25:40,391 --> 00:25:41,635
Here we go...

271
00:25:43,308 --> 00:25:44,765
"Judith Herault..."

272
00:25:45,891 --> 00:25:50,299
"Kilometer marker 98. September '82."
She was that kid?

273
00:25:50,599 --> 00:25:52,057
That's right.

274
00:25:52,308 --> 00:25:53,421
Just a sec.

275
00:25:55,141 --> 00:25:58,174
1982. It's coming back now.

276
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:04,096
She was run over by a semi...

277
00:26:04,097 --> 00:26:05,296
That's it.

278
00:26:07,016 --> 00:26:09,302
What a goddamned mess.

279
00:26:09,303 --> 00:26:11,050
Here she is.

280
00:26:12,933 --> 00:26:16,179
Here's her file, with the policemen's
statements...

281
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:20,841
pictures and all. I am warning you.
The pictures are...

282
00:26:21,558 --> 00:26:22,387
Don't worry.

283
00:26:28,558 --> 00:26:29,967
I warned you.

284
00:26:32,599 --> 00:26:34,968
Jesus. What happened?

285
00:26:34,969 --> 00:26:38,222
A 38 ton truck going 120 kilometers
an hour.

286
00:26:40,266 --> 00:26:41,971
How did you identify her?

287
00:26:41,972 --> 00:26:45,838
When we got there,
the mother was at the side of the road.

288
00:26:46,141 --> 00:26:49,145
- She was holding...
- What?

289
00:26:49,266 --> 00:26:51,261
- A finger.
- Finger.

290
00:26:52,391 --> 00:26:55,673
The only piece of her
daughter still intact.

291
00:26:58,433 --> 00:27:03,219
She said her kid ran away
and tried running across the highway.

292
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:04,553
God knows what happened.

293
00:27:04,849 --> 00:27:06,922
You don't have the mother's number?

294
00:27:06,923 --> 00:27:09,883
Are you kidding? It's been 20 years.

295
00:27:09,884 --> 00:27:12,676
The insurance company
sent us an address...

296
00:27:13,183 --> 00:27:16,880
in case we came across any new leads.

297
00:27:18,224 --> 00:27:19,682
This is too crazy.

298
00:27:31,433 --> 00:27:34,182
"University of Guernon"

299
00:29:12,308 --> 00:29:13,717
The Dean's office?

300
00:29:14,058 --> 00:29:15,965
That way, on your left.

301
00:29:35,849 --> 00:29:37,425
I want to see the Dean.

302
00:29:37,808 --> 00:29:40,047
I am his assistant. How can I help?

303
00:29:40,266 --> 00:29:42,387
By getting me the Dean, now.

304
00:29:47,224 --> 00:29:48,503
Who shall I say is here?

305
00:29:48,504 --> 00:29:50,223
Commissioner Niemans.

306
00:29:52,766 --> 00:29:54,673
Commissioner Niemans for you.

307
00:29:58,016 --> 00:30:00,718
Have a seat. I will just be a minute.

308
00:30:20,849 --> 00:30:24,760
I am a slave to this university.
I never have enough time.

309
00:30:25,224 --> 00:30:26,137
What can I do?

310
00:30:26,891 --> 00:30:28,928
I am investigating Callois's death.

311
00:30:28,929 --> 00:30:30,806
I spoke to Captain Dahmane.

312
00:30:31,433 --> 00:30:33,755
Tell me about Remy's private life.

313
00:30:33,756 --> 00:30:35,508
Do you work with Dahmane?

314
00:30:35,509 --> 00:30:39,511
Neither with nor without.
I lead a special unit.

315
00:30:42,474 --> 00:30:43,718
It's you.

316
00:30:44,599 --> 00:30:46,839
I don't understand what happened.

317
00:30:47,558 --> 00:30:50,175
Remy never posed the slightest problem.

318
00:30:50,176 --> 00:30:54,639
He was kind, hardworking.
His parents were close friends.

319
00:30:56,099 --> 00:30:59,050
He took over his
father's job in the library.

320
00:30:59,599 --> 00:31:00,972
He went to school here?

321
00:31:00,973 --> 00:31:02,716
Like most of us.

322
00:31:02,717 --> 00:31:05,509
Many students are born and grow up here.

323
00:31:05,510 --> 00:31:08,596
Some become professors like their parents.

324
00:31:08,597 --> 00:31:10,632
It's sort of the tradition.

325
00:31:11,058 --> 00:31:12,550
It was the case with Remy.

326
00:31:14,016 --> 00:31:16,800
He didn't have a police record.

327
00:31:17,058 --> 00:31:20,671
Maybe there's something we missed,
that may be of help.

328
00:31:20,672 --> 00:31:21,886
Like what?

329
00:31:23,349 --> 00:31:24,723
Someone who hated him.

330
00:31:24,974 --> 00:31:28,007
Drug use, some religious conviction...

331
00:31:28,008 --> 00:31:30,055
I think you misunderstood me.

332
00:31:30,766 --> 00:31:34,759
This university is a community,
a temple of knowledge.

333
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:38,381
Everyone lives and works here
in perfect harmony.

334
00:31:38,683 --> 00:31:41,965
To accuse one of us is to accuse
all of us, including me.

335
00:31:47,016 --> 00:31:48,888
I want to visit his apartment.

336
00:31:49,974 --> 00:31:53,719
I am afraid that's impossible.
The police sealed it off.

337
00:31:55,058 --> 00:31:57,463
I'd like to see it all the same.

338
00:32:00,516 --> 00:32:02,590
Hubert, come here, please.

339
00:32:03,183 --> 00:32:05,219
Unfortunately, I can't join you.

340
00:32:05,220 --> 00:32:08,591
I hope you don't mind
if my son shows you the way.

341
00:32:09,974 --> 00:32:13,589
As I told you,
traditions are a way of life here.

342
00:32:20,266 --> 00:32:22,884
We have been voted "Best College"
three years in a row.

343
00:32:22,885 --> 00:32:26,220
We even helped raise the national average.

344
00:32:26,221 --> 00:32:30,846
Just for fun, we calculated
the average IQ here. Guess how much.

345
00:32:30,847 --> 00:32:32,260
Twenty-four.

346
00:32:32,891 --> 00:32:33,672
Excuse me?

347
00:32:33,673 --> 00:32:36,467
Callois had room 24.
Do you have the key?

348
00:32:36,468 --> 00:32:37,589
No.

349
00:32:40,308 --> 00:32:42,594
Do you have permission to go in?

350
00:32:57,016 --> 00:32:59,385
What did he do at the library?

351
00:32:59,386 --> 00:33:02,639
He was in charge of books
and seating arrangements.

352
00:33:04,308 --> 00:33:05,966
Seating arrangements?

353
00:33:06,183 --> 00:33:10,093
Our tradition is to be seated
in the same place every year.

354
00:33:10,391 --> 00:33:13,259
It's beneficial and makes seating easier.

355
00:34:00,183 --> 00:34:03,181
"Dominissimus. Simus serve."

356
00:34:04,141 --> 00:34:05,681
"Ubicum Que..."

357
00:34:05,682 --> 00:34:08,509
"We are the masters. We are the slaves."

358
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:11,681
"We are everywhere. We are nowhere."

359
00:34:11,974 --> 00:34:14,095
"We control the crimson rivers."

360
00:34:15,599 --> 00:34:18,965
It was his Ph.D. thesis. He'd been
working on it for years.

361
00:34:31,349 --> 00:34:33,719
- Fanny Ferreira?
- Up there.

362
00:35:01,141 --> 00:35:04,056
- I have got to go.
- See you tomorrow.

363
00:35:06,849 --> 00:35:08,425
Fanny Ferreira?

364
00:35:10,224 --> 00:35:13,009
You discovered Remy Callois's corpse?

365
00:35:13,641 --> 00:35:14,837
Who are you?

366
00:35:14,838 --> 00:35:18,346
Pierre Niemans.
I came from Paris to investigate.

367
00:35:20,766 --> 00:35:22,673
Paris exports cops now?

368
00:35:23,516 --> 00:35:25,174
Depends on the case.

369
00:35:26,974 --> 00:35:31,097
Too bad. I like the local yokels.
Their seriousness cracks me up.

370
00:35:31,098 --> 00:35:32,463
Me, too.

371
00:35:33,266 --> 00:35:34,722
You can make a difference?

372
00:35:34,723 --> 00:35:38,967
I have been trying to for 25 years.
Maybe you can help.

373
00:35:39,224 --> 00:35:40,717
I doubt it.

374
00:35:41,058 --> 00:35:45,051
I didn't see much. I scaled the
cliff twice before noticing him.

375
00:35:45,974 --> 00:35:47,515
Didn't you read my statement?

376
00:35:49,974 --> 00:35:51,005
Did...

377
00:35:51,724 --> 00:35:55,468
Did the killer have to be strong
to get the body up there?

378
00:35:55,469 --> 00:35:57,217
Not necessarily.

379
00:35:57,516 --> 00:36:01,462
With know-how and good equipment,
you can lift anything, anywhere.

380
00:36:07,349 --> 00:36:08,675
What was he like?

381
00:36:08,676 --> 00:36:11,965
A pretentious asshole.
Like most students here.

382
00:36:11,966 --> 00:36:14,296
I agree. It seems pretty...

383
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:16,511
- Uptight?
- Exactly.

384
00:36:16,512 --> 00:36:19,798
A closed-circuit race course
for high-performance cars.

385
00:36:19,799 --> 00:36:21,596
If you have been around once...

386
00:36:21,597 --> 00:36:25,006
I read that you're a glaciologist.
What do you do?

387
00:36:25,007 --> 00:36:26,889
I control avalanches.

388
00:36:27,224 --> 00:36:30,755
The school's in a valley,
so I try to steer them away.

389
00:36:30,756 --> 00:36:32,259
You protect the school.

390
00:36:32,260 --> 00:36:33,675
I do my job.

391
00:36:33,676 --> 00:36:35,431
- Like Remy Callois.
- What?

392
00:36:37,141 --> 00:36:40,589
You went to, and work for the school,
like Remy Callois.

393
00:36:41,141 --> 00:36:43,297
- So?
- You're part of the clan.

394
00:36:43,683 --> 00:36:44,346
What clan?

395
00:36:44,766 --> 00:36:47,337
The elite composed of professors' kids.

396
00:36:49,433 --> 00:36:52,384
I have a busy day and
I don't like uniforms.

397
00:36:52,724 --> 00:36:54,596
Your colleagues have my number.

398
00:37:04,724 --> 00:37:06,097
It's the pathologist.

399
00:37:06,098 --> 00:37:09,014
I got the results of
the water in his eyes.

400
00:37:09,015 --> 00:37:10,888
It's rain water. Acid rain.

401
00:37:10,889 --> 00:37:12,716
- What?
- It's pretty common.

402
00:37:13,391 --> 00:37:16,672
But we haven't had any acid rain
since the 1970s.

403
00:37:16,673 --> 00:37:18,680
And it hasn't rained recently.

404
00:37:19,641 --> 00:37:21,098
I don't get it.

405
00:38:07,016 --> 00:38:09,007
- It's ice cold.
- Freezing.

406
00:38:20,266 --> 00:38:21,759
Hello, Sister.

407
00:38:23,016 --> 00:38:25,338
I am a police officer.

408
00:38:25,339 --> 00:38:28,051
Does a certain Mrs. Herault reside here?

409
00:38:31,683 --> 00:38:32,844
May I ask why?

410
00:38:35,349 --> 00:38:38,300
I am sorry. I am afraid not. I can't say.

411
00:38:38,724 --> 00:38:41,130
Sister Andrée has been here for 17 years.

412
00:38:41,558 --> 00:38:44,011
This concerns a relatively old incident.

413
00:38:44,724 --> 00:38:46,632
Could I possibly see her?

414
00:38:49,016 --> 00:38:50,212
I will see.

415
00:38:50,213 --> 00:38:51,588
Come in.

416
00:38:53,391 --> 00:38:54,800
Wait here.

417
00:39:05,891 --> 00:39:07,005
Take off your cap...

418
00:39:15,933 --> 00:39:17,840
Where do you think you are?

419
00:39:18,266 --> 00:39:19,545
My son.

420
00:39:20,599 --> 00:39:21,713
Wait here.

421
00:39:24,683 --> 00:39:26,804
Sister Andrée will see you.

422
00:39:27,099 --> 00:39:29,421
- But I should warn you...
- About what?

423
00:39:29,422 --> 00:39:33,012
You can speak to her,
but you cannot see her.

424
00:39:33,391 --> 00:39:35,795
You can listen, but you cannot go near.

425
00:39:35,796 --> 00:39:37,171
Why not?

426
00:39:38,224 --> 00:39:39,931
The Shadows, my son.

427
00:39:40,308 --> 00:39:41,884
What about the shadows?

428
00:39:43,183 --> 00:39:45,848
Sister Andrée took
the Vow of the Shadows.

429
00:39:45,849 --> 00:39:48,421
We haven't seen her for 15 years.

430
00:40:04,516 --> 00:40:05,713
Sister...

431
00:40:14,516 --> 00:40:15,760
Sister Andrée?

432
00:40:16,849 --> 00:40:18,176
Sister?

433
00:40:20,516 --> 00:40:23,680
I am a police officer from Sarzac,
just nearby.

434
00:40:24,599 --> 00:40:26,839
Your daughter is buried there, right?

435
00:40:30,474 --> 00:40:34,006
Judith was your daughter, wasn't she?

436
00:40:37,724 --> 00:40:42,346
I am here because last night
someone tried to open her tomb.

437
00:40:57,308 --> 00:40:58,848
They're coming back.

438
00:41:00,099 --> 00:41:01,261
Who?

439
00:41:02,558 --> 00:41:06,551
They're coming back
to complete their mission.

440
00:41:07,391 --> 00:41:09,133
Who are you talking about?

441
00:41:10,016 --> 00:41:11,473
The demons.

442
00:41:12,891 --> 00:41:17,383
They want to make sure Judith
won't cause them any more trouble.

443
00:41:26,141 --> 00:41:28,925
So it's these demons
who killed your daughter?

444
00:41:30,183 --> 00:41:33,216
Could you try being a
little more explicit?

445
00:41:33,933 --> 00:41:36,966
For 18 years I have been trying to forget.

446
00:41:40,099 --> 00:41:41,557
Last night...

447
00:41:42,183 --> 00:41:43,557
your demons...

448
00:41:43,933 --> 00:41:47,760
broke into the school
and stole Judith's class picture.

449
00:41:47,761 --> 00:41:50,558
I need your help to understand why.

450
00:41:51,766 --> 00:41:54,385
In order to erase every trace of my child.

451
00:41:56,766 --> 00:41:58,175
What for?

452
00:42:00,016 --> 00:42:02,220
To protect their secret.

453
00:42:05,974 --> 00:42:07,136
What secret?

454
00:42:10,016 --> 00:42:12,587
Judith's face is a threat to them.

455
00:42:18,474 --> 00:42:20,963
Please, Sister. I am sorry, but...

456
00:42:22,308 --> 00:42:26,882
can you tell me the circumstances
of your daughter's death?

457
00:42:27,558 --> 00:42:29,513
My daughter fell ill.

458
00:42:30,391 --> 00:42:33,010
We went to the hospital she was born in.

459
00:42:33,349 --> 00:42:35,968
Then the demons attacked us.

460
00:42:37,058 --> 00:42:38,965
They chased us.

461
00:42:39,808 --> 00:42:43,718
I wanted to run away,
to disappear with my daughter.

462
00:42:44,933 --> 00:42:46,722
But they found us.

463
00:42:47,891 --> 00:42:49,798
No one can escape their clutches.

464
00:42:55,891 --> 00:42:58,178
Where did you live before Sarzac?

465
00:43:01,308 --> 00:43:04,341
The nightmare began in Guernon.

466
00:43:11,599 --> 00:43:14,845
Did you try calling the police for help?

467
00:43:14,846 --> 00:43:17,137
I speak of demons...

468
00:43:17,808 --> 00:43:19,845
and you speak of police.

469
00:43:24,641 --> 00:43:27,130
There's nothing you can do for my child.

470
00:43:29,141 --> 00:43:31,712
Save your soul while you still can.

471
00:43:35,141 --> 00:43:36,385
Leave me now.

472
00:43:39,391 --> 00:43:41,346
I want to stop remembering.

473
00:43:44,183 --> 00:43:45,261
Forgive me.

474
00:44:09,974 --> 00:44:13,055
Glaciers are formed from years
of compacted snow.

475
00:44:13,056 --> 00:44:15,594
The snow is compressed into ice.

476
00:44:16,641 --> 00:44:19,639
Each season has
a corresponding stratum.

477
00:44:21,724 --> 00:44:24,342
This glacier is 200 metres deep.

478
00:44:24,343 --> 00:44:27,384
It's a huge source
of water and energy.

479
00:44:30,141 --> 00:44:33,009
The water composing it
dates back centuries.

480
00:44:38,849 --> 00:44:41,219
What's the point of studying glaciers?

481
00:44:41,933 --> 00:44:44,302
The college power plant
has a research lab.

482
00:44:44,303 --> 00:44:48,682
This glacier is sliding.
We study the risk factor it represents.

483
00:46:02,933 --> 00:46:04,176
Here.

484
00:46:13,058 --> 00:46:15,381
How far down do we have to go?

485
00:46:16,058 --> 00:46:17,171
At least 30 metres.

486
00:46:21,058 --> 00:46:25,514
Why did you choose me?
There are great guides in the area.

487
00:46:27,391 --> 00:46:30,673
They say you're the best.
And you were available.

488
00:46:31,641 --> 00:46:34,011
You enlist civilians to find murderers?

489
00:46:36,058 --> 00:46:37,847
Let's say I am picking you up.

490
00:46:43,599 --> 00:46:45,969
Put this on. Don't step on the rope.

491
00:47:09,933 --> 00:47:12,504
Welcome to the time machine,
Commissioner.

492
00:47:32,933 --> 00:47:36,761
I will compare this ice to the acid rain
you had analyzed.

493
00:47:48,766 --> 00:47:50,556
We're at the right depth.

494
00:47:54,266 --> 00:47:56,933
He must have brought us here for a reason.

495
00:47:58,141 --> 00:48:00,132
There must be a clue...

496
00:48:00,599 --> 00:48:01,796
a trace.

497
00:48:07,224 --> 00:48:09,180
Niemans, that's dangerous.

498
00:48:25,516 --> 00:48:27,720
We can't stay here.

499
00:48:28,558 --> 00:48:31,342
Water can come gushing in at any second.

500
00:48:31,683 --> 00:48:33,389
What's back there?

501
00:48:34,016 --> 00:48:35,888
Natural water canals.

502
00:48:40,474 --> 00:48:41,848
What are you doing?

503
00:48:44,349 --> 00:48:45,842
Where are you going?

504
00:49:23,599 --> 00:49:24,712
Where are we?

505
00:49:24,713 --> 00:49:26,757
An intra-glacial canal...

506
00:49:27,308 --> 00:49:30,887
dug out by the water
that feeds the power plant.

507
00:49:32,808 --> 00:49:35,012
We can't stay here. It's dangerous.

508
00:49:37,308 --> 00:49:38,587
Let's go.

509
00:49:45,724 --> 00:49:46,921
What's wrong?

510
00:50:36,183 --> 00:50:38,884
The Light Brigade. What will it be, guys?

511
00:50:38,885 --> 00:50:43,265
Nothing today.
The Chief wants to see your tenants.

512
00:50:43,599 --> 00:50:44,879
In the back.

513
00:50:49,641 --> 00:50:51,263
- What's up?
- I am coming.

514
00:50:51,264 --> 00:50:53,968
Stay here.
I will have a word with them.

515
00:50:56,766 --> 00:50:57,928
A glass of red?

516
00:51:14,558 --> 00:51:16,844
<i>Only Through Force.</i>

517
00:51:22,099 --> 00:51:23,640
Hello, gentlemen.

518
00:51:25,016 --> 00:51:27,931
I'd like to speak to the manager.

519
00:51:28,141 --> 00:51:31,422
The head honcho.
The leader of your little group.

520
00:51:31,423 --> 00:51:32,180
What for?

521
00:51:33,058 --> 00:51:35,592
Police. I am new in the neighbourhood.

522
00:51:35,593 --> 00:51:38,336
Lieutenant Max Kerkerian.
I have some questions.

523
00:51:38,337 --> 00:51:42,095
Don't bother. We know you.
We don't talk to cops.

524
00:51:42,558 --> 00:51:44,216
I will do the talking.

