792
01:15:24,099 --> 01:15:26,386
The guy who shot at me had five fingers.

793
01:15:29,433 --> 01:15:30,807
Why did he let you live?

794
01:15:31,474 --> 01:15:33,631
So I'd understand his vengeance.

795
01:15:34,974 --> 01:15:36,930
What links the three victims?

796
01:15:37,641 --> 01:15:39,678
Callois was head librarian.

797
01:15:39,679 --> 01:15:44,257
Sertys worked in the maternity ward.
Cherneze worked with the dean.

798
01:15:44,258 --> 01:15:46,305
It all leads to the university.

799
01:15:48,308 --> 01:15:49,338
I better get back.

800
01:15:50,558 --> 01:15:51,671
What about me?

801
01:15:51,891 --> 01:15:53,597
See if Judith is dead.

802
01:15:53,891 --> 01:15:55,597
I knew you'd say that.

803
01:15:56,933 --> 01:15:58,260
I get the fun stuff.

804
01:16:08,058 --> 01:16:09,883
Call me with any news.

805
01:16:21,224 --> 01:16:22,966
What are you doing here?

806
01:16:23,891 --> 01:16:26,131
Your colleagues held me for four hours.

807
01:16:26,641 --> 01:16:29,390
Sorry. Everyone's on edge.

808
01:16:30,391 --> 01:16:31,090
Want a ride?

809
01:16:32,766 --> 01:16:33,928
Sure.

810
01:17:05,849 --> 01:17:07,639
So Cherneze is dead, too?

811
01:17:08,099 --> 01:17:09,509
Did you know him?

812
01:17:10,349 --> 01:17:12,423
One of the college's last dinosaurs.

813
01:17:14,058 --> 01:17:18,051
You don't seem to appreciate
the geniuses you live among.

814
01:17:18,266 --> 01:17:20,589
I don't respect intellectuals much.

815
01:17:22,724 --> 01:17:24,798
Weren't your parents professors?

816
01:17:26,516 --> 01:17:28,590
I don't respect my parents much.

817
01:17:28,849 --> 01:17:30,342
Take a left here.

818
01:17:51,599 --> 01:17:53,092
Is anyone expecting you?

819
01:17:54,724 --> 01:17:56,964
You're a lousy Don Juan.

820
01:17:57,599 --> 01:17:58,713
- Thanks.
- No problem.

821
01:19:42,099 --> 01:19:43,426
Nice place.

822
01:19:44,183 --> 01:19:46,338
I like it. It's far from everything.

823
01:19:46,339 --> 01:19:48,470
No TV, no radio...

824
01:19:48,471 --> 01:19:50,596
even cell phones don't work.

825
01:19:51,308 --> 01:19:52,635
A grenade?

826
01:19:53,474 --> 01:19:54,422
Thanks.

827
01:19:55,058 --> 01:19:57,381
I use them to trigger avalanches.

828
01:20:01,099 --> 01:20:02,722
Are all the locals like you?

829
01:20:03,891 --> 01:20:07,755
Battling mountains
helps forge your character.

830
01:20:10,599 --> 01:20:11,796
Same goes for cops.

831
01:20:13,266 --> 01:20:14,889
Have you been one for long?

832
01:20:16,974 --> 01:20:18,254
Too long.

833
01:20:21,891 --> 01:20:23,265
Buy lighter fluid.

834
01:20:25,849 --> 01:20:26,963
I should.

835
01:20:27,641 --> 01:20:30,473
But I am trying to quit. It was a gift.

836
01:20:30,891 --> 01:20:31,969
From your ex?

837
01:20:35,558 --> 01:20:37,762
I never got married. How about you?

838
01:20:38,683 --> 01:20:40,555
Almost. With the Dean's son.

839
01:20:42,474 --> 01:20:44,015
That could never work.

840
01:20:45,724 --> 01:20:47,549
It sure was intended to.

841
01:20:49,058 --> 01:20:52,754
After three years face to face
in a reading room...

842
01:20:52,755 --> 01:20:54,348
you get close.

843
01:20:56,891 --> 01:20:59,214
Why do you hate the school so much?

844
01:20:59,808 --> 01:21:01,929
Why do you suspect me?

845
01:21:03,391 --> 01:21:04,932
You climb mountains.

846
01:21:05,766 --> 01:21:09,096
You found the first body,
helped me find the second.

847
01:21:11,183 --> 01:21:12,972
You're the perfect suspect.

848
01:21:14,974 --> 01:21:16,431
Except for one thing.

849
01:21:16,432 --> 01:21:17,512
What?

850
01:21:18,974 --> 01:21:20,135
You're incapable...

851
01:21:20,136 --> 01:21:23,389
of strangling someone for 10 minutes,
eye to eye.

852
01:21:28,891 --> 01:21:30,135
I have to go.

853
01:21:31,266 --> 01:21:32,640
Thanks for the tea.

854
01:22:34,308 --> 01:22:35,338
Hello.

855
01:22:36,599 --> 01:22:38,804
Tell me about Remy Callois's thesis.

856
01:22:42,058 --> 01:22:44,178
He talks about the myth of Olympus...

857
01:22:44,179 --> 01:22:47,300
Greek athletes
who combined mind and body.

858
01:22:48,016 --> 01:22:52,968
He refers a lot
to the Berlin Olympic games of 1936...

859
01:22:52,969 --> 01:22:56,968
when German athletes fueled
Nazi propaganda.

860
01:22:56,969 --> 01:22:58,302
And "crimson rivers"?

861
01:22:58,303 --> 01:23:00,844
Flow with the blood of perfect men.

862
01:23:02,016 --> 01:23:03,260
Blood?

863
01:23:04,724 --> 01:23:05,755
Veins...

864
01:23:07,058 --> 01:23:07,804
Commissioner.

865
01:23:08,558 --> 01:23:10,299
You want my opinion?

866
01:23:10,808 --> 01:23:15,215
Seriously, his thesis
is a potpourri of Nazi crap.

867
01:23:15,216 --> 01:23:18,672
At the end, it's like
"How To Be a Perfect Fascist".

868
01:23:18,673 --> 01:23:22,013
He explains how to create
the perfect man today.

869
01:23:22,766 --> 01:23:23,382
How?

870
01:23:23,383 --> 01:23:27,006
By combining brawny kids
with brainy ones.

871
01:23:27,849 --> 01:23:30,219
By selecting them and marrying them.

872
01:23:31,349 --> 01:23:32,890
It's called...

873
01:23:33,683 --> 01:23:34,464
eugenics.

874
01:23:34,465 --> 01:23:36,263
Eugenics, that's it.

875
01:23:36,264 --> 01:23:39,715
Like Nazis tried in some villages
during the war.

876
01:23:40,933 --> 01:23:44,049
Like at this school. Healthy minds...

877
01:23:44,641 --> 01:23:46,182
in healthy bodies.

878
01:24:21,016 --> 01:24:23,966
What are you doing?
You have no business here.

879
01:24:23,967 --> 01:24:26,546
What role did Callois play exactly?

880
01:24:27,516 --> 01:24:28,429
Excuse me?

881
01:24:29,391 --> 01:24:32,887
Callois. Sertys. Cherneze.

882
01:24:33,183 --> 01:24:34,462
It all leads here.

883
01:24:36,724 --> 01:24:38,715
What are you after?

884
01:24:39,016 --> 01:24:40,888
You suspect us, don't you?

885
01:24:42,308 --> 01:24:44,631
Victims can be guilty, too.

886
01:24:45,224 --> 01:24:46,883
Watch what you say, Niemans.

887
01:24:47,683 --> 01:24:51,131
I inquired about you.
You're on the razor's edge...

888
01:24:52,266 --> 01:24:54,884
I'd gladly put you first on the list.

889
01:24:54,885 --> 01:24:59,346
All that's stopping me is the desire
to prove you're behind it all.

890
01:24:59,347 --> 01:25:01,590
Am I wrong? Am I?

891
01:25:05,558 --> 01:25:06,588
Stop it.

892
01:25:07,224 --> 01:25:08,551
Are you crazy?

893
01:25:13,599 --> 01:25:15,222
You will be hearing from me.

894
01:25:17,933 --> 01:25:20,256
Can't I leave you alone for a minute?

895
01:25:24,224 --> 01:25:26,132
What did you find in the tomb?

896
01:25:27,808 --> 01:25:30,178
I don't know if it will be any help.

897
01:25:42,224 --> 01:25:43,421
It's not her.

898
01:25:44,683 --> 01:25:45,926
You know her?

899
01:25:46,599 --> 01:25:49,513
- She helped with the case.
- She helped you?

900
01:25:49,514 --> 01:25:52,764
To understand the meaning
of the "crimson rivers".

901
01:25:54,058 --> 01:25:56,889
They have lived in a closed circuit here
for ages.

902
01:25:56,890 --> 01:26:01,139
Inbreeding led the professors
to start having degenerate kids.

903
01:26:01,140 --> 01:26:03,546
So they needed new blood.

904
01:26:03,547 --> 01:26:05,050
New blood?

905
01:26:05,051 --> 01:26:08,885
In the maternity wing,
they replace professors' kids...

906
01:26:08,886 --> 01:26:11,890
with healthy newborn mountain babies.

907
01:26:13,224 --> 01:26:16,471
Sertys's father exchanged Fanny
with Judith?

908
01:26:16,724 --> 01:26:18,347
And plenty of others.

909
01:26:18,766 --> 01:26:20,175
What for?

910
01:26:20,516 --> 01:26:22,174
To create a superior race.

911
01:26:25,141 --> 01:26:26,255
Nazis?

912
01:26:27,974 --> 01:26:30,759
- A freaking Nazi college?
- Not a college.

913
01:26:31,974 --> 01:26:33,550
A breeding ground.

914
01:26:44,391 --> 01:26:45,386
Who the fuck is it?

915
01:26:54,141 --> 01:26:55,550
Shoot.

916
01:27:02,058 --> 01:27:03,385
Shoot.

917
01:27:06,974 --> 01:27:08,217
It's bullet-proof.

918
01:27:08,218 --> 01:27:10,181
Aim for the same spot.

919
01:27:10,683 --> 01:27:11,761
Go on, shoot.

920
01:27:12,641 --> 01:27:13,138
Shoot.

921
01:27:14,224 --> 01:27:15,054
Watch out.

922
01:28:56,308 --> 01:28:57,386
Are you okay?

923
01:29:06,724 --> 01:29:08,596
- Who's this bastard?
- The Dean's son.

924
01:29:10,183 --> 01:29:11,178
What did he want?

925
01:29:11,179 --> 01:29:14,133
To stop us from knowing
what they did to Fanny.

926
01:29:14,134 --> 01:29:17,637
What could he do to Fanny?
He was 10 back then.

927
01:29:17,638 --> 01:29:21,635
He was exchanged.
He was seated with Fanny at the library.

928
01:29:21,636 --> 01:29:24,840
He should have married her.
That was the plan.

929
01:29:24,841 --> 01:29:27,888
So then why is she killing them all off?

930
01:29:27,889 --> 01:29:30,386
She refuses to play by their rules.

931
01:29:35,391 --> 01:29:36,765
You think she's innocent?

932
01:29:49,808 --> 01:29:51,005
My coat.

933
01:29:59,516 --> 01:30:02,467
Hold on. A la Niemans.

934
01:30:19,516 --> 01:30:22,680
Who is this babe of yours?
Lady Cliff-hanger?

935
01:30:54,599 --> 01:30:55,796
Shit.

936
01:31:04,683 --> 01:31:06,223
Are you still not sure?

937
01:31:06,974 --> 01:31:08,882
To think she brought me here.

938
01:31:09,641 --> 01:31:11,431
I could have seen it all.

939
01:31:12,308 --> 01:31:14,713
She could have operated on you, too.

940
01:31:16,308 --> 01:31:18,014
She didn't want to kill me.

941
01:31:18,974 --> 01:31:20,633
She left me alive.

942
01:31:21,724 --> 01:31:23,680
What are you talking about?

943
01:31:25,474 --> 01:31:28,555
She left you alive,
but three other guys didn't make it.

944
01:31:28,556 --> 01:31:32,007
Your girlfriend's hobby is
to cut up her boyfriends.

945
01:31:32,266 --> 01:31:33,343
Why the treasure hunt?

946
01:31:33,344 --> 01:31:37,889
What are you talking about?
She's a schizoid. A psycho-killer.

947
01:31:38,849 --> 01:31:40,508
She wants us to understand.

948
01:31:41,183 --> 01:31:43,932
- What's to understand?
- She wants to get caught.

949
01:31:47,433 --> 01:31:49,968
Good news. That's our job, right?

950
01:31:50,849 --> 01:31:52,556
Now we just have to find her.

951
01:31:54,349 --> 01:31:56,139
That's our job.

952
01:32:13,141 --> 01:32:14,598
What now?

953
01:32:15,308 --> 01:32:16,716
She took the grenades.

954
01:32:16,717 --> 01:32:18,053
What grenades?

955
01:32:20,683 --> 01:32:23,171
Closed up like a fucking clam...

956
01:32:44,516 --> 01:32:46,056
Did you evacuate the college?

957
01:32:46,057 --> 01:32:48,297
I need an explanation first.

958
01:32:48,298 --> 01:32:51,638
It's not the time for explanations.
Evacuate.

959
01:32:52,308 --> 01:32:54,298
This can't go on. Who's up there?

960
01:32:55,099 --> 01:32:57,385
- I go alone.
- It's everyone or no one.

961
01:32:57,386 --> 01:32:59,050
I am going alone.

962
01:32:59,641 --> 01:33:00,919
Everyone, freeze.

963
01:33:00,920 --> 01:33:01,887
Calm down...

964
01:33:01,888 --> 01:33:03,425
No one is coming.

965
01:33:04,058 --> 01:33:05,431
Have you gone berserk?

966
01:33:05,432 --> 01:33:06,345
Give me that.

967
01:33:09,308 --> 01:33:10,884
Trust me.

968
01:33:21,391 --> 01:33:22,670
Lower your guns.

969
01:34:00,058 --> 01:34:02,048
We have to go all the way now.

970
01:34:05,516 --> 01:34:06,973
Leave her to me.

971
01:34:30,349 --> 01:34:31,511
Down there.

972
01:34:44,558 --> 01:34:46,347
Fanny, turn around.

973
01:34:47,016 --> 01:34:48,178
Come down.

974
01:34:51,183 --> 01:34:54,097
This is the end. It's over now.

975
01:34:54,683 --> 01:34:56,174
I know who you are.

976
01:34:56,175 --> 01:34:57,592
You know nothing.

977
01:34:57,593 --> 01:35:00,680
Stop it. I know what they did to you.

978
01:35:00,681 --> 01:35:02,804
Exchanging newborn babies.

979
01:35:02,805 --> 01:35:05,006
Killing kids. I know.

980
01:35:05,007 --> 01:35:08,014
It's too late.
You can't help. Go away.

981
01:35:08,015 --> 01:35:11,678
You led me here. I can't turn back.

982
01:35:11,679 --> 01:35:13,886
- Neither can I.
- Don't do that.

983
01:35:13,887 --> 01:35:17,512
They will close down the college.
They're all dead now.

984
01:35:18,058 --> 01:35:21,174
- You will kill innocent people.
- They're all guilty.

985
01:35:27,474 --> 01:35:28,801
No one is innocent.

986
01:35:30,849 --> 01:35:31,631
Judith?

987
01:35:33,766 --> 01:35:34,880
Twins.

988
01:35:35,808 --> 01:35:37,300
They exchanged twins.

989
01:35:37,641 --> 01:35:38,671
Just one.

990
01:35:39,099 --> 01:35:41,932
That's why her face was a threat to them.

991
01:35:42,933 --> 01:35:44,260
Take care of her.

992
01:35:46,641 --> 01:35:48,927
So who died in the car accident?

993
01:35:48,928 --> 01:35:50,924
What about the fingerprint?

994
01:35:52,058 --> 01:35:53,301
Mommy prepared it all.

995
01:35:53,849 --> 01:35:55,923
The other girl was already dead.

996
01:35:56,266 --> 01:35:58,173
Mommy planned everything.

997
01:35:58,849 --> 01:36:00,886
Except your going haywire.

998
01:36:00,887 --> 01:36:02,129
You thought you'd make it?

999
01:36:02,130 --> 01:36:03,965
I don't intend to make it.

1000
01:36:03,966 --> 01:36:06,630
Freeze, or you really won't make it.

1001
01:36:08,891 --> 01:36:09,388
Stop.

1002
01:36:09,724 --> 01:36:10,470
Leave her alone.

1003
01:36:12,558 --> 01:36:14,465
I will trigger an avalanche.

1004
01:36:15,849 --> 01:36:16,928
Listen to me.

1005
01:36:17,391 --> 01:36:18,172
Stay away.

1006
01:36:18,173 --> 01:36:23,090
The men who hurt you are all dead.
If you do this, they will win.

1007
01:36:35,558 --> 01:36:37,429
Only you can stop her, Fanny.

1008
01:36:37,430 --> 01:36:41,463
You're not a monster like her.
Stop before it's too late.

1009
01:36:42,558 --> 01:36:44,346
- I have no choice.
- You do.

1010
01:36:44,347 --> 01:36:45,096
Stop.

1011
01:36:51,058 --> 01:36:51,970
Kill him.

1012
01:36:58,683 --> 01:37:01,171
For our lives.
For those of our parents.

1013
01:37:01,558 --> 01:37:04,224
For the lives they stole from us.

1014
01:37:06,474 --> 01:37:07,304
Kill him.

1015
01:37:07,305 --> 01:37:09,216
- Not him. He's innocent.
- Kill him.

1016
01:37:11,683 --> 01:37:14,715
Do it for me.
For the life I never had.

1017
01:37:14,716 --> 01:37:16,797
A life in your shadow.

1018
01:37:16,798 --> 01:37:21,139
They created you.
And they rejected me. Do it.

1019
01:37:21,140 --> 01:37:22,505
Kill him, Fanny.

1020
01:37:23,641 --> 01:37:24,257
Do it.

1021
01:37:25,974 --> 01:37:28,048
You wanted him to understand.

1022
01:37:28,849 --> 01:37:30,176
You can't do that.

1023
01:37:31,349 --> 01:37:32,925
It's you and me.

1024
01:37:33,224 --> 01:37:34,172
You and me.

1025
01:37:37,058 --> 01:37:37,887
Go on.

1026
01:37:40,141 --> 01:37:40,922
Go on.

1027
01:37:42,058 --> 01:37:43,136
Don't.

1028
01:37:44,391 --> 01:37:45,386
You're not like her.

1029
01:37:45,808 --> 01:37:46,756
But I am.

1030
01:37:46,757 --> 01:37:47,762
Kill him.

1031
01:37:48,808 --> 01:37:49,423
Do it.

1032
01:37:59,391 --> 01:38:02,057
You had to understand,
so no one could forget.

1033
01:38:02,058 --> 01:38:04,132
I know.

1034
01:38:15,766 --> 01:38:16,844
Hurry.

1035
01:39:00,516 --> 01:39:01,678
Take her feet.

1036
01:40:58,099 --> 01:40:59,758
That's enough. I am fine.

1037
01:41:00,599 --> 01:41:02,092
Thanks, doggy. That's enough.

1038
01:41:03,016 --> 01:41:03,680
I have had it.

1039
01:41:07,224 --> 01:41:08,800
Can I ask a question?

1040
01:41:13,641 --> 01:41:15,632
What do you have against dogs?

1041
01:41:21,058 --> 01:41:22,432
It was a long time ago...

1042
01:42:14,500 --> 01:42:19,000
